  "text": "By the theorem above one could expect to transpose the ring structure (resp. module structure for the odd case) to the even (resp. odd) Total Twisted K-theory group via the assembly map. This is of course the case when this twisted BaumConnes map is an isomorphism. After the discussion in the last section of [CITATION_1] one might expect that this occurs whenever the untwisted Baum-Connes conjecture is verified. Another interesting question would be if it is possible to construct directly these multiplicative structures on the Total twisted K-theory groups such that the assembly map is a ring/module isomorphism. These questions will be discussed elsewhere.",
